data.name: Mockups
data.description: A mockup is a visual or tangible representation of a product, concept, or design created to demonstrate its structure, layout, and functionality. Often used in design, development, and marketing, mockups serve as a prototype or model for presenting ideas to stakeholders or end-users before full implementation. They are typically high-fidelity, showcasing the final look and feel, though they may lack interactivity. Mockups help refine design choices, gather feedback, and ensure alignment across teams. For instance, in web design, a mockup might display how a website will appear, including typography, colors, and images, without backend functionality.
